  1. Estimate a population graph for the arapat data set and visualize it in a leaflet() map.
library( popgraph )
mv <- to_mv( arapat )
pops <- arapat$Population
g <- popgraph( mv, pops )
plot(g)


strata_coordinates( arapat ) %>%
  rename( Population = Stratum ) -> coords 

decorate_graph(g, coords ) -> graph_arapat

nodes <- to_sf(graph_arapat,what="nodes")
edges <- to_sf(graph_arapat,what="edges")


library( leaflet )
leaflet() %>%
  addMarkers( data=nodes ) %>%
  addPolylines( data=edges ) %>%
  addProviderTiles(provider = providers$Esri.WorldImagery)

  1. Load in the lopho and upiga population graphs and map out each of their individual population graphs as well as the congruence_topology. What kind of inferences can you gain by looking at these levels of spatial synchrony?
data( lopho )
data( upiga )
data( baja )
lopho <- decorate_graph( lopho, baja)
upiga <- decorate_graph( upiga, baja)
plot( lopho)


plot( upiga )

cong <- congruence_topology(lopho, upiga )
